    <div class="tested-box">
      <h3>How We Tested These Omega-3 Gummies</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Purchased independently.</strong> All 20 products were purchased at full retail price through Amazon or brand websites.</li>
        <li><strong>Verified EPA/DHA content.</strong> We cross-referenced supplement facts panels for total omega-3, EPA, and DHA per serving against label claims and independent test results where available.</li>
        <li><strong>Evaluated purity certifications.</strong> Products with IFOS, NSF, or USP testing received the highest purity scores. We also checked for oxidation markers (TOTOX values) where data was available.</li>
        <li><strong>Assessed source sustainability.</strong> Fish oil sourced from small, short-lived species (anchovy, sardine) and algae-based products received higher sustainability scores than those using larger predatory fish.</li>
        <li><strong>Taste tested.</strong> Four team members evaluated each product for fishy taste, aftertaste, flavor quality, and texture over a two-week period.</li>
        <li><strong>Calculated effective value.</strong> We computed cost per milligram of combined EPA/DHA, factoring in the omega-3 form (triglyceride vs ethyl ester) and emulsification status for an adjusted absorption value score.</li>
      </ol>
